post_text:
Beebots, Ozobots, and Kubos, Oh My!

MSD is proud to have celebrated Computer Science Education Week (CSEdWeek) December 9-13 as part of an annual program dedicated to inspiring K-12 students to take an interest in Computer Science.

Computer Science is integrated into the year-long MSD curriculum in all grades, but we especially love to celebrate this week of coding, computation, and collaboration!

Originally conceived by the Computing in the Core coalition, Code.org® organizes CSEdWeek as a grassroots campaign supported by 350 partners and 100,000 educators worldwide. CSEdWeek is held in recognition of the birthday of computing pioneer Admiral Grace Murray Hopper (December 9, 1906).

Check out what great work our students have been doing! #MSDAdvantage

Has your child's experience in school been impacted by one of our district's amazing "Miracle Workers"? MHS Theatre is taking nominations now through 11/8 to honor MSD employees (Special Ed Teacher, OT, PT, or SLP), who will be recognized at the 11/22 performance of "The Miracle Worker"--the inspiring story of Helen Keller and teacher Annie Sullivan. Nomination forms are available @https://forms.gle/1Yn6Rf9YnZLQqXUo9. Tickets will go on sale soon for all performances (11/22 @7, 11/23 @2 and 7, and 11/24 @2): mhs.booktix.com.

Join the students, staff, and parents of our theatre program in this beautiful initiative! #MSDAdvantage
